discourse_list.title: Technical Update for the 2nd November Executive

content.content: Technical Update for the 2nd November Executive PECU would like to inform Maker Governance that the technical teams have decided to delay the StarkNet Fast Withdrawals component of the executive scheduled this week. This is due to some final testing checks that require additional work before deployment on-chain. PECU and SNE are meeting tomorrow (Wednesday 2nd November) to sync on our spell deployment process to ensure unified testing alignment across the various Layer2 environments. Working with the StarkNet Team and GovAlpha, the intention is to deploy StarkNet Fast Withdrawals in a future (TBD) executive pending completion of the additional testing work. A subsequent deliverable from the above meeting will be a spells-checklist to ensure sign-off of all tasks in the lead-up to deployment to make tracking tasks and sign-off easier and more transparent.
This topic was automatically closed 14 days after the last reply. New replies are no longer allowed.
